Description: Fragment of wall of pottery open vase; outside reserved, inside glazed. Incised inscription on inside.
Curator's comments: Edgar incorrectly identifies the sherd as Chian.
The fabric would seem to be Archaic East Greek, though the form of the pi suggests a later date.
Bibliographic references: Edgar 1898/1899 / Excavations at Naukratis. B: The Inscribed and Painted Pottery (no. 12)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 696, no. 534)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.340)
